&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;create-a-virtual-environment-using-python-from-pyenv&#34;&gt;Create a virtual environment using Python from pyenv&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At this point you can create the virtual environment based on Python 3.9.0 using this command &lt;code&gt;mkvirtualenv -p $(pyenv which python) py39-test&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
